[var0
		|Reeling, barely able to stand, you can’t go on — not without risking serious injury. [pc.isGrappled
			|You stop struggling and, sensing your limpness, the shalin lets go. He hovers his spread claw over you, and when you don’t try and crawl away, it descends again — this time holding you more prospectively, finding out precisely where the grabbing’s good. His tentacles descend, hooking themselves around your arms and shoulders, feathers shifting over your ears and neck. Your cheeks redden. Oh well — this is better than getting swallowed whole, you suppose.
			|The shalin lands before you with a thump. He raises his spread claw at you; when you flinch, your [pc.weapon] falling from your hand, he lowers it slowly back to the ground. Cold triumph is discernible in his unblinking eyes. He lifts his claw again, this time clutched, and raps you on the chest. Not hard enough to knock you over, but you get the picture. You fall back on your [pc.ass], and watch the great brown-striped feather-barrel loom over you. You have been subjugated to this creature’s wild will, and now he will do to you as he may.
		]
		|The mind might be strong, but the body... the body is so weak. [pc.isGrappled
			|You find yourself more caressing the claw that has you pinned to the mossy deck than fighting it, admiring its strength. As you do so, the claw reciprocates, roughly encouraging that attitude by rubbing you back and forth in the dirt. The tentacles descend, hooking themselves around your arms and trailing their soft, feathery ends over ears and neck. You sigh, allow your feeble pretensions of control to fall away, and let the wild thing do with you as he may.
			|You find yourself transfixed by the shalin’s size and strength — the physical mastery he has over this environment — and when he lands in front of you with a thump to raise his spread claw, you... no longer want to fight back. Yellow eyes silently appraise you; he takes hold of your torso, gives you a brisk shake, and your [pc.weapon] falls from your nerveless hand. Delight and anticipation leaps inside your loins as he firmly but slowly pushes you back onto the mossy ground.
		]
	]
